narratives.narrative: Property prices in Malad East have shown a gradual increase from â‚¹27,503 per sq.ft. in June 2025 to â‚¹29,396 in December 2025. Prices have remained consistently above the Mumbai Western Suburbs micromarket average, which was â‚¹21,180 per sq.ft. in December 2025. The steady rise indicates a stable price trend over recent quarters.

Compared to nearby localities, Malad East's average price of â‚¹29,396 per sq.ft. in December 2025 is lower than Goregaon East (â‚¹36,103) and Goregaon West (â‚¹33,246) but higher than Kandivali West (â‚¹25,537) and Aarey Colony (â‚¹8,569). Kandivali East shows a slight price growth of 4.96% while Malad East maintains a relatively stable price. Lokhandwala and Kandivali West have experienced price declines in this period.

In the sales market, 2 BHK units have the highest supply share at 49% but demand is lower at 36%. 1 BHK units show strong demand at 33% compared to 24% supply. Apartments dominate the sales listings with 89% supply and 90% demand. The majority of sales are in the price range of â‚¹50 L to â‚¹2 Cr, making up 45% of supply and 62% of demand. There is less demand for high-end units above â‚¹5 Cr.

For rentals, 1 BHK units are in high demand at 53% with supply at 34%. 2 BHK units have more supply (43%) than demand (19%). Apartments account for 91% of rental supply and 90% of demand. Rental listings above â‚¹50,000 make up 61% of supply but only 25% of demand. The â‚¹30,000 to â‚¹50,000 range shows balanced demand and supply.

Apartments have an average price of â‚¹29,396 per sq.ft. with a slight increase of 0.58%. Shops recorded the highest price rise at nearly 32%, while office spaces saw a decrease of 7.25%. Ready to move properties are the most common, with 347 units averaging â‚¹24,625 and a small decline in price. Under construction units show a minor price increase, and new launches have experienced a slight price drop.

narratives.highlights: Top projects by transactions include Omkar Alta Monte in Laxman Nagar with 16 sales at â‚¹29,760 per sq.ft. Ajanta CHS in Pushpa Park reported an 18% price increase to â‚¹35,476. K Raheja Heights in Sankalp Colony saw a slight price decline to â‚¹32,663. Other notable projects are Raheja Tipco Heights and K Raheja Residency in Sasankalp Colony. Projects like Shah Arcade II recorded over 26% price growth, highlighting active areas within Malad East.
